T~L~255~870~0~#979FAD~sans-serif~9pt~~~~comment~The 7-segment displays and the "dot" indicators are 
both controlled by the middle-right knob under the 
glareshield. In our implementation, the "dots" and LED 
bars within the top display section are controlled via 
the "Display Modules" circuit, whereas the 7-segment 
displays, driven by the MAX 7219 ICs are driven via 
software. In the Airbus "TEST" mode, this should not
be changed, as the brightness of the display section
doesn't change.~1~start~gge29379~0~pinpart

T~L~-475~390~0~#979FAD~~9pt~~~~comment~We need a resistor between the Arduino pin and the MOSFET gate in
this case because the Total Gate Charge is approximately 2.4nC, resulting
in an additional peak current of 8mA when switching the gate (total max 
of 38mA).
 
Target max current is 20mA (-8mA for peak headroom) = 12mA
Voltage 5
417ohm resistance needed at a minumum
 
We can use a 500ohm resistor to get a current of ~10mA (+8mA)= 18mA
Which is below the Arduino max current per I/O pin of 20mA~1~start~gge61915~0~pinpart
